The 'Falls Music & Arts Festival' (commonly known as 'Falls') is a music
festival held annually in Lorne, Victoria, and Marion Bay, Tasmania, Australia,
on New Year's Eve. While the festival is best known for contemporary music
performances, dance, comedy, theatre, circus, cabaret, as well as other art
forms, are also featured at the event. Due to the length of the event, people
bring a tent and camp out at the event; both locations have nearby beaches. Many
artists playing at the Falls Festival are traditionally of the blues & roots
genre, however it is not exclusively of this style, with rock, hip hop and
electronic style acts also playing.
